15/01/2007
STRASBOURG, France -- The European Parliament (EP) welcomed members from the newest EU member states -- Bulgaria and Romania -- on Monday (January 15th) its.
With the 18 Bulgarian deputies and 35 Romanian ones, there are a total of 785 EP members.
In other news, the new head of the Bulgarian National Security Service Ivan Drashkov officially began work on Friday, a day after the government endorsed his nomination.
Drashkov succeeds Ivan Tchobanov, who is becoming an ambassador.
(Darik, Focus, Nine o'clock - 15/01/07;
Mediapool - 12/01/07)
